 excellent organisational skills; as well as proven work experience as an HR Administrator, HR Administrative Assistant, or similar. Ultimately, you should be able to ensure that the company\u2019s HR department supports their employees while conforming to labour laws. What will the job involve? The chosen candidate will work in an office environment and or a mobile/home working set-up from 09:30 \u2013 18:30 (European hours) Monday to Friday and be required to organise and maintain personnel records, manage HR documents (e.g. employment records and onboarding guides) and update internal databases. Additional duties will include the preparation of HR documents, such employment contracts, new hire guides, reference letters and forms required by local authorities, as well as the revision of company policies, and updating a local organisation chart on a monthly basis. Should you be offered the position, you will also be required to liaise with external partners, such as insurance vendors, to ensure legal compliance; administer and capture local benefits by working with the benefits accountant; generate regular reports and presentations on HR metrics (e.g. turnover rates); and make yourself available to answer employees queries about HR-related issues, as well as assisting the payroll department and participating and supporting in HR projects and transitions. Does this seem like the career voyage for you? Super! Contact us ASAP, so we can get the ball rolling. If this is now quite the way your waves are crashing at the moment, but you\u2019d still like to get your feet wet, please get in touch on job@thejobharbour.com or +27 (0)21 447 1370. As one of South Africa\u2019s preferred multilingual recruitment specialists, we actively pursue inspiring roles for foreign language speakers, so if we know what we\u2019re looking for we can put our ear to the ground. Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItali